> I found this at the Lineage website. It has plenty of valuable information for people who might not know it all.. &lt;shrug&gt;<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> <br>
Hacking has always been a problem for all MMORPGs. Anytime a connection is made between a computer and another computer and or server there is always a chance of hacking. Lately in Lineage hacking has gone crazy. Who doesn't know someone who has been hacked? I know mad people who have been hacked. Hacking actually isn't NCInteractive's fault. So then whose fault is it? Simply yours.<br>
<br>
NCInteractive isn't at a fault because you download a file or go to webpages. NCInteractive strictly tells us all not to download or go to any webpage not listed in the FanSite section of their webpage. And for those of you who share accounts with your friends, if you were to be hacked/jacked by them you should be fully aware NCInteractive is not at fault according to their rules on passwords which states: <br>
(d) Passwords. At the time your Account is opened, you must select a password. You are responsible for maintaining the confidentiality of your password and you are responsible for any harm resulting from your disclosure or allowing the disclosure of your password or from use by any person of your password to gain access to your Account and Account ID. At no time should you respond to an online request for a password. NC Interactive will never ask for your password offline or online, except that you will be required to enter your password as part of the log-on process <br>
<br>
To be hacked you have to be infected by a hacker's file, a Trojan, or go to one of their websites. A hacker can actually get inside your computer with programs such as SubSeven, Y3K, BO, etc. They can look at any file on your computer, delete files, and even watch the screen while your looking at! Once infected, a hacker will upload a keylogger onto your computer. A keylogger is something, which logs every single key you type. So once you are infected with a hackers program he can keylog you and watch you type your user screen name and password the next time you log onto lineage. <br>
<br>
Active X has currently been a big problem here in lineage. Hackers can make webpages with Active X that infect you with a file once viewing their webpage. A hacker can then connect to you and start his hacking. Being hacked by Active X can easily be avoided just by updating the version of your Internet Explorer. Active X is a flaw in the Internet Explorer code for version 5.0 and lower. If you update the version of your Internet Explorer this will patch that bug. <br>
<br>
Downloading a file from someone in Lineage is always a mistake. If someone offers you a file you should say no. But figuring most of you wont; here is what usually happens. A hacker will offer you a file, he will tell you how great it is and why you should use it. Such as rollers. Most rollers are actually a server, a backdoor to your computer which gives a hacker full access. <br>
<br>
Ways to avoid being hacked: <br>
Don't let anyone know your password. Even your best friend in the game. This is always a common mistake. Get yourself some AntiVirus! Buy Norton AntiVirus, and update its virus definitions weekly. Download or buy a firewall. Firewalls detect any net activity. Try <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.zonealarm.com">www.zonealarm.com</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--> Patch your computer! Windows has a feature called Windows Update. This is a great tool! They are always making patches for hacks or bugs. <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://windowsupdate.microsoft.com">windowsupdate.microsoft.com</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
If you think you are infected right now from a hacker, there is an AntiVirus called Tauscan, which searches for any Trojan in your computer. You can download Tauscan for free from <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.download.com">www.download.com</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--> and search for &quot;Tauscan&quot;. <br>
<br>
Anyway have fun in the game but try not to be hacked. Don't download, don't go to webpages that aren't listed in the FanSites section, don't give out your password, and don't hold NCInteractive responsible because you run viruses/trojans and do not protect your computer.<br>
<br>
&lt;3 American<br>
